Mwanza. The Lake Victoria Environmental Management Project (LVEMP II) has set aside Sh74 billion to conserve the ecosystem and improve people s livelihoods in the Lake Zone.LVEMP II Coordinator Omari Myanza told The Citizen on Monday that projects have been implemented in Mara, Shinyanga, Mwanza, Geita and Simiyu regions. He added that economic ventures had been launched to improve the livelihood of 341,000 people in the Lake Zone.Mr Myanza mentioned the projects as beekeeping, fish farming, irrigation schemes and tree planting.He noted that 216 projects had been established and implemented in the regions.